<item>
            <title>[AMQ-4117] MQTT Inactivity Monitor doesn&apos;t respect client keep alive setting.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-4117</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The MQTT Inactivity Monitor starts its monitoring thread to early which means that it cannot honor the keepAlive time sent by the client.  The transport should wait until its received the client CONNECT command before it starts its monitoring thread. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
